The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing 3D shapes from 2D images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The method proposed in the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are also commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on 3D reconstruction suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
